The advantage of the boosting procedure is that it works on decreasing the bias of the model, without increasing the variance. Learning uncorrelated base learners helps to reduce the bias of the final ensemble model. In this work, we used the L2- TreeBoost approach proposed by Friedman35 to build the core GBM model. Here the loss function is the classical squared-loss function (L2):\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
