Here the parameter η is a regularization parameter which is used to avoid overfitting the models and is acquired via cross validation. For each iteration a, the least-squares criterion (I(ϕ)) used to assess potential splits of a current terminal region P into two disjoint sub-regions (Pl, Pr) is given by:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
